1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3-151.1, is
3 amended to read as follows:
4 Section 3-151.1. A. For purposes of establishing a uniform and
5 accurate definition of high school graduation rate for school
6 districts and secondary schools in the this state, the State Board
7 of Education shall adopt and implement a four-year adjusted cohort
8 graduation rate and an extended-year adjusted cohort graduation
9 rate. The Board shall utilize and report the four-year adjusted
10 cohort graduation rate and the extended-year adjusted cohort
11 graduation rate at the secondary school site, the school district,
12 and the state level, and the graduation rates shall be reported in
13 the aggregate as well as disaggregated by subgroups as required in
14 the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 2001 1965 (ESEA), as
15 reauthorized by P.L. No. 107-110 114-95, also known as the No Child
16 Left Behind Act of 2001 Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA).
17 B. The Board shall use the four-year adjusted cohort graduation
18 rate for purposes of determining the high school graduation rate
19 indicator for the academic performance data calculation beginning
20 with state and district report cards providing results of
21 assessments administered in the 2011-2012 school year. The Board
22 shall use the four-year adjusted cohort graduation rate for
23 establishing the high school graduation rate for measuring alternate
24
Req. No. 2158 Page 2
1 year percentage growth targets as set forth in Section 3-151.2 of
2 this title beginning with the 2012-2013 school year.
3 C. The four-year adjusted cohort graduation rate shall be
4 defined as the number of students who graduate in four (4) years
5 with a standard high school diploma divided by the number of
6 students who entered high school four (4) years earlier, adjusted
7 for transfers in and. Students who transfer out of the school,
8 émigrés or emigrate to another country and deceased students shall
9 not be included in the adjusted cohort graduation rate. Twelfth-
10 grade students who transfer into a school after October 1 of any
11 school year shall not be included in the adjusted cohort graduation
12 rate. Students who graduate in four (4) years shall include
13 students who earn a standard high school diploma at the end of their
14 fourth year, before the end of their fourth year, and during a
15 summer session immediately following their fourth year. To remove a
16 student from a cohort, a school district shall confirm in writing or
17 by electronic means that a student has transferred out of the school
18 site or school district, has emigrated to another country, or is
19 deceased. For a student who transfers out of a school site or
20 school district, the written or electronic confirmation shall be
21 official and document that the student has enrolled in another
22 school site or school district or in an educational program that
23 culminates in a high school diploma recognized by a state or private
24 higher educational institution accredited or recognized by the
Req. No. 2158 Page 3
1 Okla homa State Regents for Higher Education for purposes of
2 admission to the institution. Students who are not enrolled in a
3 program which culminates in the award of a credential recognized by
4 a state or private higher educational institution for purposes of
5 admissions shall not be included in the graduation rate calculation
6 as set forth in this subsection as a student who graduated in four
7 (4) years with a standard high school diploma but shall be included
8 in the number of students who entered high school four (4) years
9 earlier.
10 D. The extended-year adjusted cohort graduation rate shall be
11 defined as the number of students who graduate in four (4) years or
12 five (5) years with a high school diploma divided by the number of
13 students who form the adjusted cohort for the four-year graduation
14 rate as calculated as provided for in subsection C of this section,
15 provided that the adjustments add to the cohort all students who
16 transfer into the cohort by the end of the year of graduation being
17 considered and subtract students who transfer out, emigrate to
18 another country or are deceased by the end of that year. The
19 extended-year adjusted cohort graduation rate shall be reported
20 separately from the four-year adjusted cohort graduation rate.
